text: Manor Park Manor Park was the former stadium of Nuneaton Borough A.F.C.. 22,114 spectators packed into the ground for an FA Cup tie against Rotherham United in 1967. The club moved away from Manor Park at the beginning of the 2007/08 season to a new home at Liberty Way which they share with Nuneaton R.F.C.. In 2008 Manor Park was demolished and housing was built on the site. Category:Defunct football venues in England
title: Manor Park (Nuneaton)
